summary: Tampa Bay Buccaneers quarterback Baker Mayfield has filed a lawsuit against his father's company, seeking approximately $12 million in damages. The lawsuit alleges that the company, PRM Management, breached a settlement agreement that was reached in 2022. The alleged breach involves a dispute over money that Mayfield claims was stolen from him over a period of several years. The lawsuit, filed in Texas, accuses PRM Management, Mayfield's father James, and his brother Matthew of engaging in fraudulent behavior and embezzlement. Mayfield, who recently signed a one-year contract with the Buccaneers, was previously a star quarterback at the University of Oklahoma and the Cleveland Browns.

summary: Intel Corporation recently announced the unexpected retirement of its CEO, Pat Gelsinger. The company has yet to name a successor, and the search for a new CEO is underway.

name: Neal Brown
summary: West Virginia University has fired head coach Neal Brown after six seasons, in which he led the Mountaineers to just two winning campaigns. Brown's tenure was marked by a 37-35 record, with a lackluster 6-6 finish in his final season. His dismissal follows a disappointing loss to Texas Tech, which Brown described as an "ass-whooping." Reports indicate that Brown met with university leaders to discuss his future before his termination. Speculation is now rife regarding potential replacements, with several names being floated as candidates to lead the Mountaineers' football program.

name: Rockets
summary: The Houston Rockets have emerged as a dominant force in the NBA, showcasing exceptional defensive prowess. They secured a thrilling 117-111 victory over the Minnesota Timberwolves on November 26th, 2024. Experts now consider the Rockets legitimate contenders in the Western Conference, citing a resurgence in the league's health. Dillon Brooks' contract with the Rockets is also under review, while they face crucial matchups against the Philadelphia 76ers and Oklahoma City Thunder. The Rockets clinched a group victory in the NBA Cup, positioning themselves strongly to host a quarterfinal. Analysts predict a close contest against the 76ers on November 27th, with a proven model favoring the Rockets. Despite a valiant effort from Fred VanVleet, the Thunder fell short against the Rockets in their final road game, with the box score revealing a narrow 119-116 defeat.
